The paper discusses the regulation of cellular network markets, which falls under the category of computer networks and the internet (cs.NI). It also discusses the use of radio access technologies and cognitive radio approaches, which are related to information theory (cs.IT) and computer communications (cs.COM). The paper proposes a self-regulating spectrum market regime, which is related to the field of cognitive radio (cs.CR) and social and information networks (cs.SI).
